What is this game?
\n<About NPC><WordWrap>This game is called "GASTROPOLIS: A CULTURAL JOURNEY" an undergraduate thesis project made by the students at "WEST VISAYAS STATE UNIVERSITY" or "WVSU" in short.
\n<About NPC><WordWrap>This game revolves the main concept of cooking and the most common or prominent dishes of Iloilo City, hence the name Gastropolis.

\n<About NPC><WordWrap>The game includes puzzle solving, adventure or roaming aspects, learning valuable lessons and reading comprehension towards the participants, and challenging minigames for the players to play and figure out.
\n<About NPC><WordWrap>Though the game is big and vast with challenges, the game is still in Alpha development and testing due to limited time, budget, and resources.

\n<About NPC><WordWrap>NOTE: WE DO NOT GUARANTEE THAT THE GAME IS FREE OF BUGS, DUE TO THE GAME'S LARGE SCALE ENVIRONMENTS AND PUZZLES, THE RESEARCHERS WE'RE ABLE TO FIX THE MAJORITY OF ALL THE BUGS. BUT ARE NOT GURANTEE THAT ALL BUGS ARE FIXED OR ELIMINATED.
\n<About NPC><WordWrap>We do sincerily thank you for participating and playing "GASTROPOLIS: A CULTURAL JOURNEY".
Who made this game?
\n<About NPC><WordWrap>The game was made by the students of "WEST VISAYAS STATE UNIVERSITY" and created multiple assets to create the game.
\n<About NPC><WordWrap>The people who made the game are as follows:
\n<About NPC><WordWrap>HENRY NOPUETO and RIZDY HUYATID, are responsible for creating the assets and around the world of this game that ranges from characters, environments, items, music, and so on.
\n<About NPC><WordWrap>CHRISTIAN JAY RENTILLO, is the engineer of the game who made all of the corresponding functions/nodes/code, of the game and built the level designs and environment of the game.
\n<About NPC><WordWrap>KENSHIN SUPEA and NICOLE ANNE CORALL, are responsible for checking the quality of the game and testing to see if there are further bugs of the game.
\n<About NPC><WordWrap>The game is part of their undergraduate thesis project that immerses the player in the cultural foods of Iloilo CIty and engament through its gameplay and mechanics.
What is the purpose of this game?
\n<About NPC><WordWrap>The purpose of this game is to showcase and higlight the most common and famous food here in Iloilo city, as well as promoting the city's achievement.
\n<About NPC><WordWrap>The game is designed to evolve with each player feedback and is crucial to both refining the game mechanics and story for future iterations of the game.
